# Progethod

A fast timesheet entry wrapper around Wethod. Users log daily time in a minimal UI, then submit to Wethod via a Cloudflare Pages proxy.

## Tech Stack

- Nuxt 2.15 + Vue 2.6 SPA (SSR disabled, static target)
- Tailwind CSS 4, PostCSS
- Vuex + vuex-persist → localStorage (offline-first)
- @nuxtjs/axios, @nuxtjs/i18n (Italian only), @nuxtjs/date-fns
- Cloudflare Pages Functions as API proxy to Wethod
- Chrome MV3 extension for auth (reads Wethod session cookie)
- Google Calendar integration via OAuth + Magic Tags

## Key Decisions

- **Offline-first**: entries are stored in localStorage; synced to Wethod only on explicit submit.
- **Entries older than 30 days** are auto-pruned from localStorage.
- **Wethod decimal rounding**: hours are stored in 0.1h (6-minute) steps; adjustment logic redistributes residuals.
- **Components are auto-imported** (`components: true` in nuxt.config.js).
- **Monthly calendar popover**: the month label in the weekly header is clickable and opens a calendar grid showing green (8h tracked) / amber (<8h) / gray (untracked) per weekday, using Wethod tracked-hours data.
